The problem with the trials for the most part the other 47 times was people misusing mana or casters ping ponging the mobs. All casters must no how to minimize aggro. All tanks must no how to target fast. All melee must know how to assist right and quickly. If you are doing pickup groups its not easy to find a combination of players together that know their classes and their roles in doing this. It takes a group that is totally in sync to do this. Its not an easy thing to pass, if a player is power levelled through the trials, they may not be ready for the tier two zones. In fact those who are capable of passing the trials with a pickup group are capable of playing in these zones.<br>
<br>
Some of the highlights from my 50 tries in the trials...<br>
-I had a monk charge in front of me before the spawns saying that he could tank the mobs if he wanted to. Needless to say we never got past one mob.<br>
-In the first 23 tries, I had 20 tries where the casters were way on the other side of the room and not getting up with me when they cast. Needless to say, we lost each time we had to do that.<br>
-Many times we never made it passed the third round because casters were out of mana. They didn't really know how to efficiently cast nor did they know which spells to use.<br>
-Had to wait one time for 4 and a half hours to go once. Had a phenomenal group stacked with some 65 mages and high damage classes. 4 groups in front of us passed and we had to reform a couple of times. When we got to the platform and were ready a group decided to kill steal their way into the trials and they passed it. At that point our high level group disintegrated and we had to reform into a crappy group.<br>
-In 50 tries I died a total of 5 times. One time was twice in the same trials from being rezzed into a full spawn.<br>
-Each time the boss mob spawned I had to kite him to help casters and healers generate more mana. I learned the most effective way to do this is to run him all the way around the room (keeping wall on right), and stopping for a split second each time I would reach the wall farthest from the platform, then continuing again.<br>
<br>
As far as what you need to do, it might help if you and friends each hit one more level. Also go in with two rogues and an ench or a rogue and a mage and an ench or something like that. Stay away from wizzies is best advice I can give you. Most wizzies I found have levelled by quad kiting and they think Kite all the time. You can go in with a druid, but if the druid says that they are nuking only, don't trust them, they don't realize that druids have a good heal because its meant to be used. Plus these druids nuke usually because they are used to kiting as well. If your cleric friend doesn't have a good mana pool then get her or him equipment to have a large mana pool. Don't use complete heals at all until the boss mob. Use Supernal Elixur as heals or Supernal Remedy. It is lower aggro and does the healing job with less mana useage. Go in with mod rods. On the last round hold nothing back, have cleric nuke if need be. You can kite the boss mob for 30 minutes if you need  to get mana back. While you are kiting boss mob have cleric heal you with a low aggro heal each time you pass by or when you need it. Have mage kill pet right after final round until you are ready to engage the boss mob. It will aggro the boss mob before you have the mana to fight it. Get each of the casters a low level horse for medding while they fight. Don't get unlucky and draw three or four rocks in any of the rounds. Really they seem to be on a cycle. If you go in after one or two groups just passed I believe your chances of drawing a lot of rocks on one round are less. Always banish when you can. It will save your group a lot of mana. Don't do the trials with 14 year olds. Do it with college kids or with those who are mature enough and know their classes. Watch for players that know their classes well and play them well. You will want to make a group with these players at some point. Don't be stuck on having to do the trials with your friends exclusively. If one of you passes that is going to help the others. If you don't have a good group, don't go in with them. If you have a bad player in your group, leave the group. You aren't going to pass it anyways with bad players, so no reason to waste your time with them. Better to have LFG on while in there rather then being in a sorry group. One time I was asked to tank for an uber guild that was going to PL some of their players through because I had LFG on. Problem was they got one of their 65 warriors to tank it instead of me, but I did make some contact with them and they would have been willing to help me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iskandaralazeem>Iskandar Alazeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of the Battlefield</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1018<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/02 1:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trials!!!  Advice! </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showMessage?topicID=1461.topic">pub14.ezboard.com/ftheste...1461.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
