<br>
1. Get as many buffs as you can - For example if you don't have a paladin in you group get bmb from someone there or ask a friend to come buff you.<br>
<br>
2. Buy/make/steal a damage shield potion.  The easiest way to increase your dps - also stacks with a ds buff get a buff as well if no one in your group can cast a ds get one just before going in.<br>
<br>
3. Target the next mob quickly - F8 is your friend.  Time your not hitting a mob is wasted time.  Try to kill rock mobs first - but if you can don't fret it kill whatever you targeted. Do NOT switch targets you don't have time.<br>
<br>
4. DPS is important but not as important as working together.  To give you an example we got to the 3rd mob on the 4th wave with war, sk, sk, necro, enc, cler the mob was at 4% painful but would have been doable if it wasn't 4am and people just a little tired.<br>
<br>
5. In this little escapade you are in charge - don't be afraid of taking control.<br>
<br>
6. As a general rule of thumb do not allow hydras.  Sure it can be done hydra, but I don't think most people have the skill to do it.<br>
<br>
7. Everyone must stay close if everyone is close all the mobs are close.  If all the mobs are close your not wasting time running around finding your next target.<br>
<br>
8. When you are killing a mob use your F9 views and plan your next target.<br>
<br>
It can be done with a pick-up group.  After 20+ attempts I finally succeeded with a pick-up group.  Everyone must plan on doing it at least 3 times for a pick-up group to really succeed.  You'll probably fail the first time one like the first wave as everyone gets used to you being in charge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glatius2>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 601<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/02 2:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Its important for the MT to try and get agro early, having eveyone stand behind the MT is a good idea, maybe all the way to the back wall initially, while you stand near the front of the benches.<br>
<br>
Moving from target to target quickly is more important than selecting a particular target (as was previously said).  If you see a likely mob nearby that would make an attractive target, go for it, otherwise just pick the closest.<br>
<br>
Have anyone with cure disease keep it up, having the slows cured as quickly as possible is important.<br>
<br>
Everyone must work on killing the same mob at the same time, no exceptions.  There is very little room for error on this.<br>
<br>
Crowd control is nice, but not required.  Root crowd control can and does work.  AE slows are nice as well if you have a shaman available.<br>
<br>
Have the cleric use CH only on the boss mob at the end.  Otherwise heals over time usually are the better choice.<br>
<br>
The Warrior really needs to save their defensive discipline for the boss mob, he hits hard and fast.  <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
