<br>
i stand between the benches with everyone else back near the execution platform.  as soon as they spawn i mash my /target a_dark hotkey and if there is one, it will be targeted and i jump on him right away.  then i hit F9 while i'm fighting him to see what the other 3 mobs are.  if it's just the fiends, i just F8 the rest of the mobs when the stone guy is dead.  if there's more stone guys, i mash my target hotkey again and jump on the next stone guy.  i usually kill named ones last since they have a bit more HP and thus the dammage shield hitting them the whole fight will help by the time i get to him.<br>
<br>
make sure when you're clerics heal or shamans slow or chanter CC, that they are standing right next to you.  if they're doing it from the platform, the mobs are gonna run after them, and you'll lose valuable time having to run to them.  don't let your healers heal you when you're low health because it will cause bad aggro for them, and there's no room to pull aggro off anyone and still win the fight unless war has AE taunt.<br>
<br>
DO NOT use defensive before boss mob, no matter how bad things look, you'll need it for him at the end till he gets slowed.<br>
<br>
don't bring people who can't follow directions or are kinda lazy/slow reaction players.  i also don't recommend bringing anyone lower than level 58. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=breoganeq>BreoganEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/02 3:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.terra.es/personal5/entilzha/Wolf.jpg width=100 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trials!!!  Advice! </span><hr size=1> Last time I did it flagging a friend was:<br>
<br>
61 Cleric (No PoP spells), 61 Shaman (No PoP spells), 64 Ranger (EQ / AM3), 63 Ranger(EQ / AM3), 59 Mage (No epic) and 64 Paladin.<br>
<br>
We teared through the trial. I was playing wife's ranger (63 one) to get her flagged and did it pretty fast. We failed 1st attempt because the group that failed Exe before us didn't leave the room, and when we ported up our cleric got left behind. Managed to make it to 3rd wave before we lost our shaman tho <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Usually paladin would sit before each wave started, so when the mobs spawned all came for him. Then shaman would cast Tigirs on the mob the paladin had chosen (getting the others too) and tanks 2 of the mobs. The mage puts the pet in one of the adds and helps with nukes to kill the paladin's mob and the rangers assist him.<br>
Rangers used disc on 3rd and 4th wave respectively, to help with mana for the named executioner.<br>
<br>
