<br>
Was pretty funny <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11869&amp;resize=true">Breogan Wolfheart</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.tunare-europa.co.uk/tide">Overlord of Tide</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brokkah>Brokkah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/02 9:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trials!!!  Advice! </span><hr size=1> My group was 61 cleric, 61 warrior (me), 61 druid, 60 enc, 61 ranger (no EQ or AM3, tried trueshot but arrows were poofing), 62 bst (with paragon). Epic/HoT level gear, no special toys really. I had a 60 shaman buff us before we went in, + primal avatar on the ranger right before we ported in. I'd never done it before but the other guys had tried it.<br>
<br>
We had everyone huddle up in between the benches, nearest the end where exe spawns. When a wave spawned I picked a target and started on it. Generally if we only had 1 rock i would leave it to be banished later, but if we got 2 i would start on one immediately. Each mob after that was F8 target, call assist instantly. We had the enc chain stunning so dmg taken was minimal. The druid called the pace of the fight by watching the executioner, and slowing/upping the pace of nukes, or if needed banishing a rock. Cleric did heal over time and added nukes when exe got close to prisoner.<br>
<br>
1st attempt we failed on the last mob of wave 4, by about 2 seconds, due to the bst getting dazzled and a resisted banish.<br>
<br>
2nd attempt was flawless to 4th wave when the enc died, but bst pet off tanked a bit whilst we cleared the final few.<br>
<br>
Boss mob I'm ashamed to say I died to enrage lol. Still we had enough juice left in the group to finish him off <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baledoricewalker>Baledor Icewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/02 10:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.terstai.net/images/Balepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trials!!!  Advice! </span><hr size=1> One other thing, Keep your cleric up. If you die you can still get flagged if the cleric lives and can res you in. They have to cast res twice on the corpse, 1st cast will pop you to the tribunal area and 2nd cast will bring you into trial area. Res is the only way to get in before the body poofs and you lose the work you have done.  <p><img src="http://www.terstai.net/~terstai/images/Baledorsig2.jpg"><BR> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=402751" target="_blank">My Stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azlanaicelander>Azlana Icelander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sexies Warlady in all o'Norrath</BR>     ...an da moon too!</BR>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 505<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 6:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ringofshadows.org/images/Azlana7.jpg width=96 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Trials!!!  Advice! </span><hr size=1> M'thinks dey should rename trials as 'Trial o'Patience an Determination' <br>
